test:
  commands:
    - gtk-encode-symbolic-svg --help
    - gtk-launch --help
    - gtk-query-immodules-3.0
    - gtk-update-icon-cache --help
    - gtk-query-settings
    - where gtk-builder-tool
    - if not exist %PREFIX%\\Library\\include\\gail-3.0\\libgail-util\\gail-util.h
      exit 1
    - if not exist %PREFIX%\\Library\\include\\gtk-3.0\\gdk\\gdk.h exit 1
    - if not exist %PREFIX%\\Library\\include\\gtk-3.0\\gdk\\win32\\gdkwin32window.h
      exit 1
    - if not exist %PREFIX%\\Library\\include\\gtk-3.0\\gtk\\gtk.h exit 1
    - if not exist %PREFIX%\\Library\\lib\\pkgconfig\\gail-3.0.pc exit 1
    - if not exist %PREFIX%\\Library\\lib\\pkgconfig\\gdk-3.0.pc exit 1
    - if not exist %PREFIX%\\Library\\lib\\pkgconfig\\gtk+-3.0.pc exit 1
    - if not exist %PREFIX%\\Library\\lib\\pkgconfig\\gdk-win32-3.0.pc exit 1
    - if not exist %PREFIX%\\Library\\lib\\pkgconfig\\gtk+-win32-3.0.pc exit 1
    - if not exist %PREFIX%\\Library\\bin\\gailutil-3-vs16.dll exit 1
    - for /f "usebackq tokens=*" %%a in (`pkg-config --variable=exec_prefix --dont-define-prefix
      gail-3.0`) do if not exist "%%a/bin/gailutil-3-vs16.dll" exit 1
    - if not exist %PREFIX%\\Library\\lib\\gailutil-3.lib exit 1
    - for /f "usebackq tokens=*" %%a in (`pkg-config --variable=libdir --dont-define-prefix
      gail-3.0`) do if not exist "%%a/gailutil-3.lib" exit 1
    - if not exist %PREFIX%\\Library\\bin\\gdk-3-vs16.dll exit 1
    - for /f "usebackq tokens=*" %%a in (`pkg-config --variable=exec_prefix --dont-define-prefix
      gdk-3.0`) do if not exist "%%a/bin/gdk-3-vs16.dll" exit 1
    - if not exist %PREFIX%\\Library\\lib\\gdk-3.lib exit 1
    - for /f "usebackq tokens=*" %%a in (`pkg-config --variable=libdir --dont-define-prefix
      gdk-3.0`) do if not exist "%%a/gdk-3.lib" exit 1
    - if not exist %PREFIX%\\Library\\bin\\gtk-3-vs16.dll exit 1
    - for /f "usebackq tokens=*" %%a in (`pkg-config --variable=exec_prefix --dont-define-prefix
      gtk+-3.0`) do if not exist "%%a/bin/gtk-3-vs16.dll" exit 1
    - if not exist %PREFIX%\\Library\\lib\\gtk-3.lib exit 1
    - for /f "usebackq tokens=*" %%a in (`pkg-config --variable=libdir --dont-define-prefix
      gtk+-3.0`) do if not exist "%%a/gtk-3.lib" exit 1
    - if not exist %PREFIX%\\Library\\share\\glib-2.0\\schemas\\gschemas.compiled
      exit 1
    - if not exist %PREFIX%\\Library\\share\\icons\\hicolor\\icon-theme.cache exit
      1
    - if not exist %PREFIX%\\Library\\lib\\gtk-3.0\\3.0.0\\immodules.cache exit 1
  requires:
    - pkg-config
    - pygobject
  script: run_test.py
about:
  description: 'GTK is a multi-platform toolkit for creating graphical user interfaces.

    Offering a complete set of widgets, GTK is suitable for projects ranging

    from small one-off projects to complete application suites.

    '
  dev_url: https://gitlab.gnome.org/GNOME/gtk
  doc_url: https://developer.gnome.org/gtk3/
  home: http://www.gtk.org/
  license: LGPL-2.0-or-later
  license_family: LGPL
  license_file: COPYING
  summary: Version 3 of the Gtk+ graphical toolkit

  copy_test_source_files: true
  feedstock-name: gtk3
  final: true
